        "title": "feat: improve MCP operator workflows",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add MCP operator workflows for adding, configuring, enabling/disabling, probing, reloading, and logging into configured MCP servers.\n- Add config/runtime support for server enablement, tool filters, request/connect timeouts, parallel tool-call hints, OAuth, scoped HTTP headers, TLS verification, and client certificates.\n- Document the MCP CLI/config surface and cover the new runtime, projection, OAuth credential lifecycle, and CLI mutation paths with focused tests.\n\n## Verification\n\nBehavior addressed: MCP operators can manage configured servers, tune runtime behavior, authorize OAuth-backed HTTP servers, clear stored OAuth credentials, and project the same config into agent runtimes safely.\n\nReal environment tested: local focused tests/typecheck; Crabbox AWS Linux for live MCP server E2E and changed-gate proof.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/mcp-oauth.test.ts src/agents/mcp-http-fetch.test.ts src/agents/mcp-transport.test.ts src/cli/mcp-cli.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core.tsbuildinfo`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n- Crabbox AWS live MCP E2E against real npm MCP servers: `run_4d0ac1a4b74b`\n- Crabbox AWS changed gate: `run_3925ad1a00a5` with `git fetch origin main --deepen=100000 || git fetch origin main --depth=100000; pnpm check:changed`\n\nEvidence after fix: autoreview clean; focused tests passed; core typecheck passed; `run_3925ad1a00a5` exited 0; live E2E run exercised add/probe/filter/disable/enable/timeout/parallel/OAuth config/reload flows against real MCP servers.\n\nObserved result after fix: configured MCP servers honor operator controls in runtime and CLI flows, OAuth credentials are scoped and cleaned on auth clear/unset/replacement, and HTTP TLS/header behavior stays scoped to the MCP resource origin.\n\nWhat was not tested: full browser-based third-party OAuth callback with a real provider; the SDK-backed login/exchange and local credential lifecycle are covered by unit/transport tests.\n",
